+
+## Correctness
+The implementation of `_submit_prediction` correctly uses `replicate.predictions.create` as requested. It extracts `model` (or `version`) and `input` from the request object, mapping various field names (`model_name`, `inputs`). It properly wraps exceptions into `ReplicateAPIError` and extracts the HTTP status code and `Retry-After` header.
+
+## Completeness
+The implementation covers both `httpx`-style and `replicate-SDK`-style failure objects. It also handles cases where the SDK is not installed. 8 new regression tests were added to cover the new functionality, including end-to-end retry engagement.
+
+## Consistency
+The code follows the existing patterns in the `senseweave` generation module. The use of `_request_field` and `_derive_inputs` helper functions ensures a flexible API that matches the established `generate(self, request: Any)` signature.
+
+## Security
+No security issues were found. API tokens are handled via the class constructor and passed to the Replicate client. No secrets are logged.
+
+## Quality
